\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 3 | T-003 | Implement R1 Metric Accent: per-beat-position velocity multiplier applied only to non-grid-locked melodic/accent voices. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-012 | — | - `render/rules/metric_accent.py` applies 16-step 4/4 table [1.00, 0.82, 0.92, 0.80, 0.95, 0.80, 0.90, 0.78, 0.97, 0.80, 0.91, 0.78, 0.94, 0.80, 0.90, 0.78] with meter-aware extension to 3/4, 6/8, 5/4, 7/8<br/>- rule skips ostinato + perc by role filter<br/>- tests verify velocity distribution matches table on 4/4 melodic passage and is unchanged on ostinato |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 4 | T-004 | Implement R2 Phrase Arch (Todd/KTH): parabolic tempo + loudness arch over each phrase, modulated by section envelope. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-013 | — | - `render/rules/phrase_arch.py` computes tempo_mult(x) = 1 + k·(-4·(x-peak)² + 1)·tempo_deviation_pct/100 and matching amp_mult for normalized phrase position x<br/>- defaults: tempo_deviation_pct=4, peak=0.6, k=1.0<br/>- arc_shape parameter supports parabolic, cosine, asymmetric-Bezier, flat, inverted variants<br/>- composes multiplicatively with SectionEnvelope.tempo_base at each event<br/>- tests verify arc shape, peak position, and multiplicative composition |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 5 | T-005 | Implement R3 Agogic Accent: lengthen + emphasize notes at local contour apex or harmonic-charge peak. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-014 | — | - `render/rules/agogic.py` detects contour apex (up-down peak) and harmonic_charge peak per phrase<br/>- at apex: duration multiplied by 1.05–1.15, velocity +3–6 dB<br/>- only one apex accent per phrase to avoid caricature<br/>- tests verify apex detection, magnitude, and one-per-phrase rule |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 6 | T-006 | Implement R4 Duration Contrast: exaggerate short-vs-long by log(dur_ratio_to_median), melodic roles only, capped at ±10%. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-015 | — | - `render/rules/duration_contrast.py` applies log-scaled multiplier within [0.90, 1.10] on melodic voices<br/>- ostinato / perc skipped<br/>- tests verify short notes shortened, long notes lengthened, and cap enforcement |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 7 | T-007 | Implement R5 Final Ritardando: Friberg–Sundberg square-root tempo curve over last 20–30% of cadential phrases. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-016 | — | - `render/rules/final_rit.py` applies tempo(x) = v₀·√(1 - α·(x-x_start)/(x_end-x_start)) for cadential phrases only<br/>- α default 0.35, onset position default 0.75 of phrase length<br/>- triggered only when is_cadential=True on phrase<br/>- tests verify curve shape, onset position, and non-application on non-cadential phrases |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 8 | T-008 | Implement R6 Punctuation + Breath: lengthen terminal note at phrase boundary and insert breath silence of breath_after_ms. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-017 | — | - `render/rules/punctuation.py` multiplies terminal-note duration by 1.15–1.40 and inserts breath drawn from Gauss(breath_after_ms, 0.1·breath_after_ms)<br/>- breath counts against R10 silence budget<br/>- tests verify terminal-note extension, breath insertion, and budget accounting |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 9 | T-009 | Implement R7 Articulation Shaping: per-note gate-time by style (legato 0.95–1.02, normal 0.7–0.85, staccato 0.3–0.5, staccatissimo 0.15–0.25) with contour adjustments. | T1 | 5 | 3 | CCH-018 | — | - `render/rules/articulation.py` sets dur_sec as gate_time × nominal<br/>- repeated-pitch notes slightly shorter (×0.92); notes after upward leaps slightly longer (×1.05)<br/>- tests verify gate-time range per style and contour adjustments |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 10 | T-010 | Implement R8 Microtiming Polish: per-note Gaussian jitter σ=3 ms on melodic, 1 ms on ostinato, 0 ms on grid-locked machine