\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 14 | T-014 | Build the metric battery: IOI CoV, velocity σ, DNVR/DNODR, pitch-class entropy H1, Grooving Similarity (GS), tempo autocorrelation ρ₁, LZ76 compression ratio, novelty peaks per phrase, silence-at-phrase-boundaries. | T1 | 5 | 3 | CCH-034 | T-001 | - `render/metrics.py` computes each metric on PerformedPart<br/>- tooling: partitura for score I/O, mir_eval for segmentation, MusDr/MusPy for symbolic metrics, librosa for audio-rendered SSM + Foote novelty, madmom for beat/tempo cross-check<br/>- documented pass bands from the research: IOI CoV 0.04–0.12, velocity σ 12–22, DNVR 0.25–0.7, pitch H1 2.3–3.0, GS 0.6–0.9, tempo ρ₁ 0.7–0.95, LZ76 0.4–0.7, ≥1 novelty peak per phrase, ≥100 ms silence at phrase boundaries<br/>- tests run metrics on rule-disabled flat-line control (should fail pass bands) and full-stack render (should pass) |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 15 | T-015 | Build anti-pattern tests: quantization ghosting, dynamic compression, motif ossification, random-as-expression (Ljung-Box), symmetric-arc uncanny, dead-silence failure. | T1 | 6 | 3 | CCH-035 | T-001 | - `render/antipatterns.py` implements each detector<br/>- quantization ghosting: velocity σ > 0 AND timing σ < 3 ms → fail<br/>- dynamic compression: velocity range < 20 → fail<br/>- motif ossification: GS > 0.95 across repeated sections → fail<br/>- random-as-expression: Ljung-Box fails to reject white noise on tempo or velocity series → fail<br/>- symmetric-arc uncanny: per-phrase worm convex-hull shape variance < 5% across phrases → fail<br/>- dead-silence failure: no rests ≥200 ms in a 2-minute melodic passage → fail<br/>- each detector has a positive fixture (should fail) and negative fixture (should pass) |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 16 | T-016 | Implement performance-worm logger: 2D trajectory in tempo–loudness space + convex-hull area computation as CI artifact. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-036 | T-001 | - `render/worm.py` emits per-piece worm JSON and PNG to `artifacts/worms/<piece_id>/`<br/>- convex-hull area computed via scipy.spatial.ConvexHull<br/>- reject point-worm (mechanical: area < 1.0) and space-filling worm (random: area > saturation threshold)<br/>- CI attaches worm PNGs to build artifacts for listener review |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 17 | T-017 | Integrate metric battery + anti-pattern detectors into CI gate with fail-on-regression policy. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-037 | T-001 | - pytest gate runs metrics on a curated fixture set of 5-minute rendered pieces<br/>- any metric outside pass band or any anti-pattern trigger fails the build<br/>- pass bands are per-intent-tag where applicable (withhold-tagged phrases allow lower velocity σ)<br/>- tests verify a deliberately broken render fails the gate and a healthy render passes |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 18 | T-018 | Embed rule-stack provenance in exported audio metadata (e.g., WAV iXML chunk or sidecar JSON) for listener-review workflow. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCH-039 | T-001 | - each rendered audio file gets a `.render.json` sidecar with Event list, rule_stack per event, PerformanceIntent per phrase, SectionEnvelope per section, seeds, delta_track path<br/>- format documented in `my-claw/docs/render-audio-sidecar.md`<br/>- tests verify sidecar presence, schema, and ability to replay from sidecar alone |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 11 | T-011 | Implement anti-pattern detectors: `sampler_dominating` (sampler event count > 0.6 × total events) and `sampler_silent_quintet_member` (sampler used in <5% of last 50 pieces, mode-weighted). | T1 | 7 | 3 | CCS-030 | T-001 | - integrated into `render/antipatterns.py` (CCH-015)<br/>- `sampler_dominating` fires per-piece, surfaces in metrics gate as warning (downgrade to MUST FIX after 3 consecutive)<br/>- `sampler_silent_quintet_member` fires across rolling window of last 50 pieces; mode-weighted means the threshold scales with `sampler_density` per mode (so working_ambience never trips it)<br/>- tests verify each detector with synthetic piece histories |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 12 | T-012 | End-to-end smoke test on cypherclaw: capture a known room sound, watch the composer self-quote it within 3 pieces, verify the self-listener observes the resulting peaks. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCS-031 | T-001 | - `my-claw/tests/test_sampler_e2e.py` (skipped on CI, runs on cypherclaw via `pytest -m cypherclaw_e2e`)<br/>- plays a 4-second sine sweep through the speakers, lets contact/room mic capture it, waits for the daemon to detect+tag, forces the composer to compose 3 short pieces, asserts at least one of them dispatched a sampler with the captured sample<br/>- self-listener observes nonzero peak in the expected scene<br/>- documented in `docs/sampler-smoke-test.md` |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 13 | T-013 | Update `docs/cypherclaw-musicianship-roadmap.md` to reflect the quintet, document the sampler architecture in `docs/cypherclaw-sampler-architecture.md`, and add a one-page artistic-intent doc `docs/cypherclaw-sampler-artistic-intent.md`. | T2 | 5 | 6 | CCS-033 | T-001 | - musicianship roadmap mentions the quintet and sampler-as-memory<br/>- architecture doc covers the data model, daemon, dispatch, effects bus, and selector<br/>- artistic-intent doc captures the three usages (memory of place, self-quotation, found library) and the five principles<br/>- docs link from each other; mkdocs / repo nav updated if applicable |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-**Sprint 2 total:** ~24 hrs\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Sprint 2 total:** ~12 hrs\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\