po elasticity modulates phrase-level shaping. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-026 | T-011 | - at each event, final_tempo_mult = section_envelope.tempo_base(t) × phrase_arch.tempo_mult(x) × (1 + sensor_tempo_scale)<br/>- clamp composed result to ±15% bounds<br/>- tests verify multiplicative composition and clamp behavior |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 26 | T-026 | Implement tempo-dependent swing curve per Friberg/Sundström (3.5:1 at slow tempi down toward 1:1 at fast), with short-note near-constant ~100 ms. | T1 | 6 | 3 | CCH-027 | T-011 | - swing ratio computed from current tempo rather than fixed global setting<br/>- short-note duration held near 100 ms across tempo range<br/>- optional role-specific override (cymbal uses ride ratio, soloists use Benadon BUR 1.2–1.7)<br/>- tests verify ratio curve and short-note invariance |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 27 | T-027 | Add arc-shape variety so not every phrase uses a symmetric parabola: per-phrase random selection from parabolic/cosine/asymmetric-Bezier/flat/inverted with peak-position variance. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCH-028 | T-011 | - arc_shape selected from PerformanceIntent or, if unspecified, sampled from authored distribution weighted by intent_tag<br/>- for intent_tag=withhold, occasional flat arc (tempo_deviation_pct=0) is expressive<br/>- tests verify shape distribution over many phrases and flat-arc presence for withhold intent |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 28 | T-028 | Implement restraint parameter enforced as global dampener across rules. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCH-029 | T-011 | - PerformanceIntent.restraint ∈ [0, 1] scales: tempo_deviation_pct (× (1-restraint)), dynamic_range_db (× (1-restraint·0.7)), silence-budget thresholds (× (1 + restraint))<br/>- R2, R10 read restraint at runtime<br/>- tests verify restraint=0 is neutral and restraint=1 produces near-flat phrases with extended silence |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-**Sprint 3 total:** ~30 hrs\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 14 | T-014 | Add systemd unit `cypherclaw-sample-capture.service` that runs `sample_capture_daemon.py` with `Restart=always`, dependent on `cypherclaw-jack.service`. | T2 | 3 | 6 | CCS-020 | T-011 | - unit file at `my-claw/systemd/cypherclaw-sample-capture.service`<br/>- `User=user`, `LimitMEMLOCK=infinity`, `ExecStart=/home/user/cypherclaw/.venv/bin/python3 /home/user/cypherclaw/tools/sample_capture_daemon.py`<br/>- `After=cypherclaw-jack.service`, `Requires=cypherclaw-jack.service`<br/>- enabled on boot via `cypherclaw_boot.sh`<br/>- daemon survives a 30-minute soak test with simulated JACK xruns |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 15 | T-015 | Implement TDD-grade test fixtures with canned 1-second audio windows representing each detector branch (silence, footsteps, dishwasher, music, dogs, transient cluster) for fast deterministic CI. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCS-021 | T-011 | - `my-claw/tests/fixtures/sample_capture/` directory with WAV fixtures<br/>- `test_sample_capture_daemon.py` exercises each fixture against the detector and asserts expected flag<br/>- fixtures are short (≤2 s) and committed to repo so CI does not need real JACK<br/>- documented as the way to add new detector cases |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 16 | T-016 | Wire `SampleSelector` into `cast_planner.select_cast_ids` so when the cast includes `sw_sampler`, a sample is pre-selected for the piece and attached to the cast metadata. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCS-022 | T-011 | - `select_cast_ids` (or a sibling `assemble_cast`) returns cast entries with optional `sample_record: SampleRecord` field for sampler voices<br/>- selection happens once per piece commission and passes mode + arc_phase + mood + target_character (drawn from `instrument_patches.select_instrument_patch`)<br/>- tests verify sampler voices in cast carry a sample_record and that the record matches selector contracts |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 17 | T-017 | Per-mode sampler density gates: composer plays `floor(sampler_density * total_phrases) + Bernoulli(sampler_density)` sampler events per piece (clamped 0..total). | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCS-023 | T-011 | - `tools/duet_composer.py` reads `mode_sampler_density` and schedules sampler events accordingly within the song's tracker timeline<br/>- evening_reflection at 0.65 produces noticeably more sampler events than working_ambience at 0.10 in 100-piece simulated runs<br/>- never schedules more sampler events than total phrases in the piece<br/>- tests verify density-to-count math, clamp behavior, and per-mode separation |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 18 | T-018 | When a human plays the MIDI keyboard or Theramini for >5 seconds during a song, capture that input phrase to `samples/keyboard/` or `samples/theramini/` with full tagging. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCS-024 | T-011 | - `sample_capture_daemon.py` listens for keyboard/theramini activity via existing state files (`/tmp/midi_keyboard_activity.json`, `/tmp/theramini_state.json`)<br/>- on >5-second sustained play, captures the corresponding window from the appropriate JACK input<br/>- tags include `human_player` (e.g. `anthony` if face_recognition supports it, else `unknown`), `instrument` (`midi_keyboard` / `theramini`), and the inferred key the human played in<br/>- tests verify trigger threshold, source routing, and tag inclusion |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 19 | T-019 | Sample-aware harmonic planning: when a sample with known `pitch_hz` is selected, transpose to fit the current piece's key by computing the closest in-key root and applying `pitch_transpose_semitones`. | T1 | 5 | 3 | CCS-025 | T-011 | - `sampler_dispatch::transpose_to_key(record, key_name) -> semitones` returns the integer transposition that maps `record.pitch_hz` to the nearest pitch in the current key (B-rooted modes preferred)<br/>- when `record.pitch_confidence < 0.4`, transposition is set to 0 and the sample plays \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"atonally\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" as a texture<br/>- tests verify transposition for known pitch + key combinations, low-confidence pass-through, and edge cases (octave wraps) |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 20 | T-020 | Add per-mode effects-bus presets: solitary/evening favor more reverb + delay; working_ambience uses minimal effects; storm uses high freeze + heavy comb-B. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCS-026 | T-011 | - `sampler_dispatch::FX_PRESETS_BY_MODE: dict[str, dict]` mapping mode name to fx args<br/>- solitary: `delay_time=0.6, delay_feedback=0.65, verb_mix=0.45, freeze_amount=0.2, comb_b_amount=0.4`<br/>- companion: `delay_time=0.5, delay_feedback=0.4, verb_mix=0.3, freeze_amount=0.0, comb_b_amount=0.15`<br/>- working_ambience: `delay_time=0.3, delay_feedback=0.2, verb_mix=0.15, freeze_amount=0.0, comb_b_amount=0.1`<br/>- evening_reflection: `delay_time=0.7, delay_feedback=0.55, verb_mix=0.5, freeze_amount=0.15, comb_b_amount=0.3`<br/>- storm: `delay_time=0.25, delay_feedback=0.7, verb_mix=0.25, freeze_amount=0.55, comb_b_amount=0.6`<br/>- tests verify each preset, that values are within SynthDef-acceptable ranges, and that `dispatch_sample` correctly applies the preset for the active mode |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 21 | T-021 | Surface \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"currently sampling X\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\