ck)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThese are the top reasons tasks get PASS WITH NOTES instead of clean PASS.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nAvoid them on the first attempt:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- **Always include a migration** when adding or modifying database columns.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  A new model or column without a migration is a deployment gap.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- **Commit all changes** before the verify phase begins. Uncommitted work\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  is flagged as blocking by the verifier.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- **Stay in scope** — only commit work under this task's ID. Do not bundle\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  changes from adjacent subtasks or refactor unrelated code.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- **Add indexes on new FK columns** in `__table_args__` when adding\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  foreign key relationships.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- **Keep CHANGELOG entries consistent** with actual behavior. Do not copy\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  descriptions from other tasks or specs without verifying they match\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  the implemented code.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Validation\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nRun before final commit:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```bash\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\npip install -e '.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x && ruff check src/ tests/ && mypy src/\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nAll must pass.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Candidate Hardening (Auto-Generated)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nUse the recurring failure patterns below as mandatory hardening checks:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Runtime does not invoke bootstrap_identity on startup, so the identity file is never guaranteed to be created automatically at first run. Severity: blocking.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Add bootstrap_identity() invocation in startup flow (before FirstBootAnnouncer) so first boots mint and persist identity automatically..\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Ensure this path is u